        "**How to find outliers:**\n",
        "\n",
        "The Interquartile Range (IQR) method is a common way to identify outliers in a dataset.\n",
        "\n",
        "Step 1: Sort the data\n",
        "\n",
        "Original data:\n",
        "50, 60, 45, 67, 78, 10, 101, 77, 88, 89\n",
        "\n",
        "Sorted data:\n",
        "10, 45, 50, 60, 67, 77, 78, 88, 89, 101\n",
        "\n",
        "step 2: Find Q1 and Q3\n",
        "\n",
        "There are 10 values (an even number), so split into two halves:\n",
        "\n",
        "Lower half: 10, 45, 50, 60, 67\n",
        "Upper half: 77, 78, 88, 89, 101\n",
        "\n",
        "The median of each half is:\n",
        "\n",
        "Q1 = 50\n",
        "Q3 = 88\n",
        "\n",
        "Step 3. Calculate IQR:\n",
        "\n",
        "IQR=Q3−Q1=88−50=38\n",
        "\n",
        "Step 4. Calculate Outlier Boundaries\n",
        "\n",
        "Lower fence:\n",
        "\n",
        "Q1−1.5×IQR=50−1.5(38)\n",
        "=50−57=−7\n",
        "\n",
        "Upper fence:\n",
        "\n",
        "Q3+1.5×IQR=88+57=145\n",
        "\n",
        "Step 5. Identify Outliers\n",
        "\n",
        "Any value:\n",
        "\n",
        "Less than −7, or\n",
        "Greater than 145"
      ],
